24/04/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev and Romanian counterpart Calin Popescu Tariceanu spoke by phone Friday (21 April), discussing co-ordinated efforts against flooding. 
According to media reports in Sofia and Bucharest, they focused on managing the situation along the Danube, where record levels caused disastrous flooding last week. 
Tariceanu and Stanishev decided to put the interior and administration ministers of the two countries in permanent contact regarding co-ordinated activities, so future damage can be minimised. 
(bTV - 22/04/06; BNR - 21/04/06)
